  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, then peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and <strong>half</strong> your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a pot with a matching lid with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat and once hot, add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong>, <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pot and cook for 2-3 min or until crispy</p><p>Once crispy, carefully pour the oil into a heatproof bowl and set aside, reserving the pot – this is your <strong>crispy chilli oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1678182426960-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1678182426960-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1678182426960-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1678182426960-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1678182426960-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>sushi rice</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold running water </strong>for 30 secs (use your hands to really wash the grains!), then set aside to drain fully</p><p>Add the <strong>drained rice</strong> with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml]</span><strong> cold water</strong> to the reserved pot and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low until very gently bubbling and cook, covered, for 15 min</p><p>Tip: Don't peek! Keep the lid on the whole time to get fluffy and sticky rice!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1678182435659-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1678182435659-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1678182435659-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1678182435659-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1678182435659-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After 15 min, remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for a further 10 min before serving</p><p>While the rice is cooking, add your <strong>diced chicken thigh</strong> to a large bowl with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>soy sauce</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and set aside to marinate</p><p>Soak your <strong>skewer[s] </strong>in <strong>cold water</strong> (this prevents them from burning whilst cooking)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1678182443732-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1678182443732-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1678182443732-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1678182443732-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1678182443732-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the grill to medium-high</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and grate your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and grate the <strong>remaining garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>grated garlic & ginger</strong>, <strong>remaining soy sauce </strong>and <strong>toasted sesame oil </strong>in a bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> – this is your <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1678182452829-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1678182452829-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1678182452829-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1678182452829-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1678182452829-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>(enough to cover the whole base of the pan)</p><p>Add your<strong> cornflour</strong> to the <strong>marinated chicken </strong>and give everything a good mix up until the chicken is fully coated</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated chicken</strong> and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until golden, crispy and cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>karaage chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1678182460732-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1678182460732-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1678182460732-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1678182460732-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1678182460732-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, drain your <strong>king prawns</strong>, then add them to the <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong> and mix all together until the prawns are fully coated</p><p>Thread the <strong>coated prawns</strong> onto the <strong>soaked skewer[s]</strong>, then add to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray and put the tray under the grill for 4-5 min, turning half way or until cooked through – this is your <strong>teriyaki prawn skewer</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1678182471372-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1678182471372-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1678182471372-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1678182471372-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1678182471372-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>sriracha </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and <strong>mayo</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>sriracha mayo</strong></p><p>Rinse your <strong>blanched edamame beans</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>rinsed</strong> <strong>edamame beans</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>sriracha mayo </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>edamame salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1678182480459-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1678182480459-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1678182480459-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1678182480459-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1678182480459-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>karaage chicken </strong>and the <strong>teriyaki prawn skewer </strong>with the <strong>sushi rice</strong>, <strong>edamame salad </strong>and <strong>remaining sriracha mayo </strong>to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Pour your <strong>crispy chilli oil</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) over the sushi rice</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
